document.title: Ohio's Early Learning and Development Standards

532803DE527141C699F8C81D05114684.description:
Make marks and “scribble
writing” to represent objects
and ideas.

B0E043C51A4F4FD4A679CFF10962D915.description:
Begin to use thumb and fingers
(5-finger grasp) of one hand to hold
writing tool.

D7DB92CC80A445DC8E17ED5B516F0EB6.description:
With modeling and support,
recognize own name in print.

AECFB9C33FE84DA89EA9D5D87783110C.description:
With modeling and support,
recognize familiar logos and
environmental print.

87D75D456E694A08BAEF9D0B8D423115.description:
Distinguish between sounds that
are the same and different (e.g.,
environmental sounds, animal
sounds, etc.)

0E95C379EC484A0785307117F8AE7047.description:
Distinguishes pictures from
letters and words in a text.

D7C68EB4F5624690802F3F5AFF850048.description:
Demonstrate a beginning
understanding that print
carries meaning.

31C125A16C4941539B210D522C191055.description:
Understand when words are used
in unconventional ways during
shared reading.

0552434612D343A1B42F74C62B6A1B95.description:
Use pictures to describe and predict
stories and information in books.

811FFC2C350C4A98A097FD3F8179242C.description:
Demonstrate an understanding
of the meaning of stories and
information in books.

6A4C42FAE52B434E897AD270C6E1DA04.description:
Show an appreciation for reading
books, telling stories and singing.

181197C4F59C48A3B24E28A898BEA84B.description:
Participate in and often initiate
communication according to
commonly accepted expectations
with family members and in
social groups.

73C2625BD72F4F1B868D3F99E7D78984.description:
Use words that indicate
position and direction.

723AB40419A0477BB41570BE76007D31.description:
With modeling and support,
describe experiences with
people, places and things.

60E4675535B548B6A74FD0B347748964.description:
Combine words to express
more complex ideas,
or requests.

6862FE93FD294258ABD6234995321BEB.description:
Understand when words are
used in unconventional ways.

C61B78AA57A948968B79EBC803E6C75C.description:
Demonstrate interest in and
use words that are new or
unfamiliar in conversation
and play.

9870AF405FB64913B17BD93135FA7F03.description:
Show understanding of
requests and statements
referring to people, objects,
ideas and feelings.

77A2272D42194FB5AB0FC68B9E7A3942.description:
Demonstrate understanding that
events have a cause.

EC41D9F30B044886A5B21E5F54A41151.description:
With modeling and support,
use simple tools to explore the
environment.

F58A7BC2675C4DBC811B4E6819BA41A5.description:
Ask questions about objects and
events in the environment.

E681B18AE7F543369FEF2202585CEE5B.description:
Engage in focused observations
of objects and events in the
environment.

09D587D8127D4C15B3F3E3228F5ACE10.description:
Engage in sustained and
complex manipulation of objects.

6C6115DD2D494961B591F32D49139BE4.description:
Identify self and others as
belonging to one or more groups
by observable characteristics

AB82BB4080334F56BFB8B64F27461687.description: Cognition and General Knowledge: Social Studies

BDAE7374460D4EC1B0BF79B9A6A8B9B4.description:
Demonstrate how things fit
together and/or move in space
with increasing accuracy.

13B0670468F542F19225B28F64A6FAE6.description:
Demonstrate awareness that
objects can be compared by
attributes (e.g., size, weight,
capacity), and begin to use
words such as bigger, smaller
and longer.

57A93B4927E742BDA8A79249D5032B31.description:
Copy and anticipate a
repeating pattern.

E5ECBDFEF30A446FB1666A3633672C12.description:
Sort objects into two or more
groups by their properties
and uses.

234A5DD3002D49AF93DD40858F92A681.description:
Place objects in one-to-one
correspondence relationships
during play.

5062630F09EE4E9AA5B36F957B523142.description:
Demonstrate an understanding
that “adding to” increases the
number of objects in the group.

455142DEA271450990CD8CAD05D1FEB0.description:
Use number words to indicate
the quantity in small sets of
objects (e.g., 2, 3), and begin
counting aloud.

3081E3C273784CBB935E424FCFBFD140.description:
Show understanding that
numbers represent quantity and
demonstrate understanding of
words that identify how much.

CEB199BB213B4E17AF7D81439F7B92FE.description:
Engage in pretend play involving
several sequenced steps and
assigned roles.

B0961D05139B44F792F8EE4134EB07A4.description:
Reenact a sequence of events
accomplished or observed at
an earlier time.

F725F8F89A394F828FFD8A6DED881169.description:
Recall information over a longer
period of time without
contextual cues.

7107AB5B0F7343EEB5FE23EA41F3986C.description:
Use adults as resources when
needing help in potentially
unsafe or dangerous situations.

83B117EFDA684807AA84FD9C40B4710F.description:
Cooperate and/or stop a
behavior in response to a
direction regarding safety.

0BC976D808C34C0894C97086FF3CBFCC.description:
With modeling and support,
complete personal care tasks
(e.g., hand-washing, dressing,
toileting, etc.).

1005D47797B243369F5340115669614E.description:
Make simple food choices,
have food preferences and
demonstrate willingness to try
new foods.

C4320CF34F3844F1BB925857F65F44D2.description:
Participate in active physical
play and structured activities
requiring spontaneous and
instructed body movements.

1E60751D593648649D8C2166D25F1829.description:
Name, point to and move body
parts when asked.

C3E34A3556724074B399CC41D9DE69A4.description:
Use sensory information to guide
movement to accomplish tasks.

688F1C9C408841599B1B99C39B40881F.description:
Take bites from whole
foods, coordinate chewing
and swallowing.

93B04E9DB81E410D8455EDC00E36BD45.description:
Coordinate the use of arms, hands
and fingers to accomplish tasks.

093E56E450F34B7887020C595075EC25.description: Small Muscle: Touch, Grasp, Reach, Manipulate

8FBEE0656CAD48C08021D5769730A019.description:
Use a variety of non-locomotor
body movements (hands in the
air, turn around, stand on one
foot, etc.) during play.

8568AB0DBB0748189BCB930F233D660D.description:
Use locomotor skills with
increasing coordination
and balance.

F36303157B4C4B059D7D2E01DB32B755.description:
Use self-selected materials
and media to express ideas
and feelings.

96B5471A29854B1F93016A96979E7132.description: Expression of Ideas and Feelings Through the Arts

0564728C8891455D8E35A2CE953D5DA7.description:
Use materials in new and
unconventional ways.

6884BCD708F443BCBD10C46A75121055.description:
Engage in self-initiated activities
for sustained periods of time.

F1C2865662A846FBA81D0B97D3892DAC.description:
Focus on an activity for short periods
of time despite distractions

D1FAA7DEB1A142208D36A3652A79F435.description:
Use previous learning to inform
new experiences with people and
objects in their environment.

59DFBF61A8754741AB6515898A5B2B4C.description:
Make choices to achieve a
desired goal.

D4EA501338D346129C8A7D9E6F871EA9.description:
Experiment in the environment
with purpose.

3DDE6B968AC94038BB39DEB26D2CC443.description:
Respond in caring ways to
another’s distress in some
situations.

E33B2D02A9DD429C883EC6BDDE820CCA.description:
Demonstrate awareness that
others have feelings.

76F59BDC80A64EB5B2C5DFB920EA69A7.description:
With modeling and support,
demonstrate socially competent
behavior with peers, such as
helping, sharing and taking turns.

4A6CDE61EAA54F4AA70649EEE55365F6.description:
Engage in associative play
with peers.

8EFD8F7879F14BF7B194C66F44EFFDE4.description:
Demonstrate early signs of interest
in unfamiliar adults.

007BEAB8839D4E54BD79D0AE85A6240C.description:
Interact with familiar adults in
a variety of ways.

37AEE737550546D383C4EB4A601804CE.description:
Seek security and support from
familiar adults when distressed.

856F371283554C91BED3C690F869D2A6.description:
Display signs of comfort during
play when familiar adults
are nearby but not in the
immediate area

D591BBE440624FF0A20EA5945B3E3515.description:
Recognize own abilities and
express satisfaction when
demonstrating them to others.

4B6A26719FD640F1AC4D97223618C535.description:
With modeling and support,
manage actions and emotional
expressions.

639E8671DC4D49469985B694F1028F35.description:
Anticipate the need for comfort
and try to prepare for changes
in routine.

C2B0CFFFCC354908823EF0D31DD53964.description:
Identify own feelings, needs
and interests.

71CA09B3550444F1A70D98E3113B8F82.description:
Show awareness of themselves as
belonging to one or more groups.

09F99A4369014C3382CD857591905A9B.description:
Show awareness of own emotion
and use nonverbal and/or verbal
ways to express complex emotions
such as pride, embarrassment,
shame and guilt.
